The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 IIM-B to take more students

 Bangalore, Oct. 11 (PTI): The Indian Institute of Management here has decided to increase the number of students from the 2005-06 academic year, institute director Prakash G. Apte said today.

 In case of the post-graduate programme in public policy and management, the IIM will increase its student intake from 30 to 40-45 from 2006-07. 

 To accommodate the students, a 160-room hostel block is being constructed. The first phase comprising 60 rooms is nearing completion and the remaining will be ready by the end of this year, Apte said.

 In addition to the setting up of a post-graduate programme in software management in Chennai, the IIM is examining the possibility of such an arrangement in Hyderabad.




